\section{The \texttt{topics} subcommand}

Topics are scoped to a single stream, so the command takes the stream
name as a required positional argument.
The Zulip API method [[get_stream_topics()]] expects a numeric stream
identifier, so we first resolve the human-readable stream name via
[[get_stream_id()]].

<<functions>>=
def add_topics_command(subparsers):
    """Register the topics subcommand."""
    p = subparsers.add_parser(
        "topics",
        help="list topics in a stream"
    )
    p.add_argument(
        "stream",
        help="stream (channel) name"
    )
    p.set_defaults(func=topics_command)
@

Resolving the stream name first keeps the CLI ergonomic while still
using the API endpoint that returns the canonical topic list.
We sort the output alphabetically so repeated invocations remain stable
and easy to pipe through other tools.

<<functions>>=
def topics_command(client, args):
    """List topics in a stream."""
    result = client.get_stream_id(args.stream)
    if result["result"] != "success":
        print(f"Error: {result.get('msg', 'unknown error')}",
              file=sys.stderr)
        sys.exit(1)

    result = client.get_stream_topics(result["stream_id"])
    if result["result"] != "success":
        print(f"Error: {result.get('msg', 'unknown error')}",
              file=sys.stderr)
        sys.exit(1)

    for topic in sorted(result["topics"], key=lambda t: t["name"]):
        print(topic["name"])
@

Let's verify that topic listing resolves the stream name and sorts the
topics.

<<test functions>>=
def test_topics_lists_topics_in_sorted_order(capsys):
    client = MagicMock()
    client.get_stream_id.return_value = {
        "result": "success",
        "stream_id": 17,
    }
    client.get_stream_topics.return_value = {
        "result": "success",
        "topics": [
            {"name": "Weekly check-in"},
            {"name": "Announcements"},
            {"name": "Lab 1"},
        ],
    }
    args = argparse.Namespace(stream="general")
    topics_command(client, args)
    output = capsys.readouterr().out
    lines = output.strip().split("\n")
    assert lines == ["Announcements", "Lab 1", "Weekly check-in"]
    client.get_stream_id.assert_called_once_with("general")
    client.get_stream_topics.assert_called_once_with(17)
